<L>__{exterior barton cottage garden day}
<A>__{thomas and the carter are carrying a small piano up the path.}
<L>__{interior barton cottage parlour day}
<A>__{they carry the piano into the parlour and to the dashwoods' joyful astonishment it fits perfectly. mrs dashwood reads out the letter that has accompanied it.}
<C>__{mrs dashwood}
<D>__{'at last i have found a small enough instrument to fir the parlour. i expect to follow it in a day or two, by which time i expect you to have learned the enclosed. your devoted friend, christopher brandon.'}
<A>__{mrs dashwood hands marianne the letter and a broadsheet song.}
<C>__{margaret}
<D>__{he must like you very much, marianne.}
<C>__{marianne}
<D>__{it is not just for me! it is for all of us.}
<A>__{all the same, she looks conscious of the truth.}
